criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Elective non-cardiac surgery;

          -  Age 18-80 years;

          -  Surgery expected to last >2 hours;

          -  General anesthesia with endotracheal Intubation;

          -  Volatile anesthesia;

          -  BMI < 38 kg/m2;

          -  ASA physical status 1-3.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Weight < 45 kg;

          -  Unstable blood pressure;

          -  Known esophageal deformity or evidence of esophageal trauma or esophageal disease that
             in the opinion of the attending anesthesiologist precludes safe use of ECD.
